Definitions & Theorems (thmtools)

Use thmtools to define theorem-like environments. Number within sections for clarity.

\declaretheorem[name=Definition,numberwithin=section]{definition}
\begin{definition}[Vector Space]
A set V with operations + and scalar multiplication satisfying axioms.
\end{definition}

Figures with graphicx

Use figure environment, label below caption. Use \centering.

\begin{figure}[h]
\centering
\includegraphics[width=0.6\textwidth]{example-image}
\caption{Demo figure}\label{fig:diagram}
\end{figure}

Tables with booktabs

Use top/mid/bottom rules; avoid vertical lines.

\begin{table}[h]
\centering
\begin{tabular}{ll}
\toprule
Quantity & Value\\\midrule
Mass & \SI{1.0}{\kilogram}\\
Time & \SI{2.0}{\second}\\\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\caption{Example table}\label{tab:example}
\end{table}

Lists with enumitem

Customize labels and spacing with enumitem.

\begin{itemize}[left=*,nosep]\item First\item Second\end{itemize}

Margins with geometry

Set 1in margins for readability.

\usepackage[margin=1in]{geometry}

Links with hyperref

Enable PDF metadata and links.

\usepackage[hidelinks]{hyperref}
